      <h3>Dehydration Costs You More Than You Think</h3>
      <p>The research is consistent: a body weight loss of just 2% through sweat measurably impairs aerobic performance, reduces power output, slows reaction time, and degrades decision-making. At 3-4%, these effects become severe. Most athletes are operating in a mild state of dehydration for the majority of their training sessions without realizing it.</p>
