      <p>Sweat is not pure water - it contains sodium, potassium, magnesium, calcium, and chloride in meaningful concentrations. Drinking plain water to rehydrate during and after intense training can actually dilute blood sodium levels, blunting the drive to drink and slowing fluid retention in the cells where it is needed. Electrolytes are not optional - they are part of the hydration equation.</p>
