      <ul>
        <li><strong>Sodium:</strong> Primary electrolyte for fluid balance and neural signaling. Heavy sweaters can lose 1-2g per hour. 200-500mg per training hour is a reasonable target.</li>
        <li><strong>Potassium:</strong> Works opposite to sodium to regulate cell hydration and muscle contraction. Low potassium is linked to cramping and reduced endurance capacity.</li>
        <li><strong>Magnesium:</strong> Involved in over 300 enzymatic reactions including ATP production, protein synthesis, and muscle relaxation. Deficiency is extremely common in athletes.</li>
        <li><strong>Calcium:</strong> Critical for muscle contraction, nerve signaling, and bone density - particularly relevant for female athletes and high-impact sports.</li>
